  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\n```\r\nerigon version 2.49.2-stable\r\n```\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n```\r\nLinux Ubuntu 2204 latest\r\n```\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config)\r\n```\r\n/usr/local/bin/erigon --chain=goerli \\\r\n  --datadir=/data/erigon \\\r\n  --torrent.download.rate=125mb \\\r\n  --maxpeers 15 \\\r\n  --private.api.addr=localhost:9090 \\\r\n  --metrics.addr=0.0.0.0 \\\r\n  --metrics.port=6060 \\\r\n  --pprof \\\r\n  --pprof.addr=0.0.0.0 \\\r\n  --pprof.port=6061 \\\r\n  --internalcl\r\n```\r\n\r\nConcensus Layer: Internal CL\r\n\r\nChain/Network: Goerli\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nCL Download History resumes from block number where process stopped last time.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nBlock number reverted when restarting node process.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nRestart node process.\r\n\r\nCurrently, syncing Goerli archive node with Internal CL.\r\nInitially, I ran node without `--internalcl` flag, added it later because block sync stopes at `0x81b31f`.\r\nAs we can see in the first image, Download history progress reached to `5951279` after leaving it for about 4~5 days. However, restarting node reverts progress to `6636192` (2nd image). \r\n\r\n(Before Restart)\r\n<img width=\"1469\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2023-10-01 at 16 58 46\" src=\"https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/assets/28953860/163d0fcc-87c2-46ff-9d3a-c7cb1b1ec952\">\r\n\r\n(After Restart)\r\n<img width=\"1460\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2023-10-01 at 16 58 23\" src=\"https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/assets/28953860/a8bd7ed0-21bd-4a4e-b1d1-666b955fe8a2\">\r\n\r\n",
